    "Additionally, novel metrics such as Logical Consistency Score (LCS) and Rule Adherence Score (RAS) are proposed to evaluate the model's efficacy in applying symbolic reasoning: LCS (Logical Consistency Score) = # of logically consistent responses Total # of responses (5) RAS (Rule Adherence Score) = # of responses adhering to rules Total # of responses (6) These metrics are not only instrumental in evaluating the correctness of information retrieval but also provide insight into the quality and reliability of the responses generated by TinyLlama.",
    "The performance evaluation culminates with a comparative analysis against established baselines, providing a robust understanding of the enhancements the hybrid architecture contributes to the model.",
    "This section presents the findings of your research.",
    "Benchmark Task Performance ComparisonThe evaluation of both the original and improved TinyLlama models across the selected BIG-bench tasks reveals a discernible enhancement in performance metrics.",
    "The enhanced TinyLlama demonstrates a consistent increase in accuracy across all tasks, underscoring the efficacy of the integrated symbolic reasoning layer.The comparative analysis indicates that the incorporation of symbolic reasoning contributes to an overall boost in performance, with particularly notable improvements in tasks requiring a high degree of logical deduction and rule-based processing, such as Analogical Reasoning and Mathematical Reasoning."
